NEW dates May 8-12, 2023
Moms of Rising Stars
www.momsofrisingstars.com
Are you a Christian mom with a talented child and you are curious in knowing more about pursuing a career in the entertainment industry? You may have concerns about protecting their faith and values. 
I am hosting a 5-day  challenge May 8-12, 2023
“Spotlight Your Child’s Dreams” 
Connecting the dots from here to Hollywood.
Over the 5 days I will offer resources, community with other moms, encouragement in confidence and mindset, and support to guide your child while helping them maintain their faith.
We will explore keys like identity and confidence, and the importance of community and family and tools for you to overcome obstacles and thrive with your child while building their dreams. 
With my own personal journey and experience and a shared faith, let me help you cultivate courage, empowerment, an
d influence to support your child's unique talents and interests. 

My vision is to create a community of confident and informed moms who are equipped to guide their children through the entertainment industry, while protecting their well-being, fostering strong relationships, and making a positive impact on the world."

Come join me and other moms in the 5 day challenge and let’s see where we can go from here! 

#onechildatatime #dreams #momsofrisingstars #Hollywood

💥 ⭐️ 💥⭐️💥⭐️💥⭐️💥⭐️ I wanted to share what I’m working on these days and a NEW project I’m launching called Moms of Rising Stars. I’m SO excited! It’s taken me 10 months to piece this together and I’m working on more to add on. This is a huge stepping into more of the destiny God has on my life to impact moms of 8-17 year old talented kids and encourage and support them to stand strong in their faith and values as they discover their child’s dreams. 

There’s a workshop on March 17th “Faith, family and Hollywood Dreams: Empowering Christian moms in the entertainment industry. 
and then I’m hosting my 5 day challenge April 10-14 called Spotlight Your Child’s Dreams: “Connecting the Dots from Here To Hollywood. 

If you know any moms who fit this please invite them in. I would love to meet them and be a positive impact on their journey. 💛momsofrisingstars.com

Another hero left the frontlines of this earthly battle
A stalwart and noble man
A Family man
One of a kind
He gave above and beyond his duties 
He called it privileged to serve 
I’ve met no other like him

He fought and gave it his all 
He embraced love, life, love and laughter. 
A general 
Other soldiers on duty…on the battlefield came from far and wide to hear the incredible stories of valor he would share 
Not a dry eye in one moment and not a silent space but a room filled with boisterous laughter in another. 
This mighty man of strength touched a multiplicity of hearts and lives who will never be the same 
He stands tall among them all
In my eyes he will forever be my hero! 

Stacey Collins

I love you dad!! ❤️❤️ Miss you! 💔😭

Nov 22, 2023

11/22 and today I’m 55!! They say I’m officially a “senior” lol

This year I felt that it would be a different year than usual and it really has been. As I posted yesterday some of the greatest birthday gifts are forgiveness and love. 

I am experiencing a sense of new and unexpected in beautiful and hard ways!! 

This year I say goodbye to my dad. He was 22 years old when I was born.
Born on September 22nd and I was born November 22nd. He 77 and me 55 this year. 

My mom and I had a scheduled flight for November 21st and then our flight from yesterday was canceled for mechanical failure. Praise Jesus they discovered it! So today I spend my birthday with the one who birthed me….my mom….how cool is that! 
Flying from calgary to Toronto at 6 am mst….arriving at 11:55 am est…..then a 3 hour wait for a nice birthday lunch at the Toronto airport….then flying to Sault Ste. Marie, Ontario and arriving at 4 pm est. 

Others in my family are doing a caravan trip from calgary to Ontario. 

There’s something really special and yet sombering about this time….this birthday….

I’m thinking of dad now up in heaven and saying goodbye for us here on earth and yet seeing new beginnings and life continuing forward! How can we even grasp this. 

I know this is another journey through grieving….through ashes…..through the valley of death….

So as I celebrate being born on this day….I also celebrate my dad being birthed into eternal life in heaven. 

My heart is heavy and my heart is full!!! A depth of loss so great I can’t comprehend it….unfathomable…..
My heart also  feels joy knowing my dad knows Jesus and is now with Him in that beautiful place….heaven….

“Happy birthday” has taken on a new meaning for me. I’m seeing God turning things intended to crush and bringing them for good….but oh the pain…oh  the grieving….oh the birthing…..

Dad this is my first birthday without you here to sing “Happy Birthday to me…..happy birthday to me” I miss you dad but I know you are singing “hallelujah what a Saviour!!!” with all the chorus of angels. 

#happybirthday2023 #55 #amazinggrace #glorybound
